{{Politics of the Falkland Islands}}
This is a '''list of by-elections to the [[Legislative Assembly of the Falkland Islands|Legislative Assembly]] and the [[Legislative Council of the Falkland Islands|Legislative Council]] of the [[Falkland Islands]]'''. The [[Legislative Council of the Falkland Islands]] was founded on 13 November 1845, originally as an entirely appointed body. The first elections to the council took place in [[Falkland Islands general election, 1949|1949]]. The Legislative Assembly replaced the Legislative Council with the implementation of the new [[Constitution of the Falkland Islands|Constitution]] on 1 January 2009.

The Legislative Assembly consists of eight elected members, five from [[Stanley (constituency)|Stanley]] and three from [[Camp (constituency)|Camp]]. Under section 32(2) of the [[Constitution of the Falkland Islands|constitution]], if an elected member of the Legislative Assembly vacates their seat for any reason other than a [[dissolution of parliament|dissolution of the Assembly]], there is a by-election to fill the empty seat. The by-election must be held within 70 days of the vacancy occurring, unless the Assembly is due to be dissolved within 126 days.

==Legislative Assembly==
The [[Falkland Islands general election, 2009|first election]] to the newly constituted Legislative Assembly took place on 5 November 2009 and the assembly was dissolved on 17 October 2013 in preparation for the [[Falkland Islands general election, 2013|2013 general election]].

===Stanley, December 2011===
[[Emma Edwards]], MLA for [[Stanley (constituency)|Stanley]], resigned from the Legislative Assembly on 21 October 2011 following her decision to leave the Falklands.<ref>{{cite news |title=Falklands Councillor, Emma Edwards, resigns from Legislative Assembly |author= |url=http://en.mercopress.com/2011/10/24/falklands-councillor-emma-edwards-resigns-from-legislative-assembly |newspaper=[[MercoPress]] |date=24 October 2011 |accessdate=28 December 2013}}</ref> Her seat was filled by Dr [[Barry Elsby]] in a by-election on 15 December 2011.<ref name="MercoPress Bio">{{cite news |title="We are in a war of attrition… and we can’t let Argentina win", says Falklands MLA |author= |url=http://en.mercopress.com/2011/12/16/we-are-in-a-war-of-attrition-and-we-can-t-let-argentina-win-says-falklands-mla |newspaper=[[MercoPress]] |date= 16 December 2011 |accessdate=28 December 2013}}</ref>
