==Legislative Council==
===Stanley, 2008===
A by-election took place in the [[Stanley (constituency)|Stanley constituency]] on 3 January 2008 after the incumbent councillor, Richard Andrew Davies, became Chief Medical Officer. There was controversy over the circumstances that led to the by-election as Richard Davies had been advised by the Government that he could take on the office of Chief Medical Officer without forfeiting his seat in the Legislative Council. However, this was later deemed to be unconstitutionally, forcing Davies to give up his seat. Davies sort re-election at the by-election, but lost out to [[John Birmingham (politician)|John Birmingham]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Falkland Islands: Penguin News weekly update |author= |url=http://en.mercopress.com/2007/11/23/falkland-islands-penguin-news-weekly-update |newspaper=[[MercoPress]] |date=23 November 2007|accessdate=27 April 2014}}</ref> This was the last election to the Legislative Council prior to it being reconstituted into the Legislative Assembly on 1 January 2009.

