{{unreferenced|date=January 2018}}
[[Image:Meenmutty Falls.jpg|Meenmutty Waterfalls|thumb|left]]
'''Meenmutty Falls''' is a [[waterfall]] located {{convert|45|km}} from [[Trivandrum city]] in [[Thiruvananthapuram District]] in the Indian state of [[Kerala]], [[India]]. The falls are located near the [[Neyyar Dam|Neyyar Reservoir]] area. No transportation is available so visitors have to trek 2km through the dense forests to reach the falls. It is very beautiful fall with beautiful surroundings.  The [[Kombaikani Falls]] lie {{convert|2|km}} upstream of the Meenmutti Falls on the trek path to [[Agastyakoodam]]. 

[[File:Meenmuty waterfall, Thiruvananthapuram.JPG|thumb|Meenmuty waterfall, Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala]]

{{coord missing|Kerala}}

