{{Infobox protected area | name = Naejangsan National Park | alt_name = 내장산국립공원, 內藏山國立公園 | iucn_category = II | photo = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = | photo_width = | map = | map_alt = | map_caption = | map_width = | location = | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coord|35.432|N|126.896|E|region:KR|format=dms|display=inline,title}} | coords_ref = <ref>{{Cite web| url=http://protectedplanet.net/sites/Naejangsan_National_Park| title=Naejangsan National Park| website=protectedplanet.net}}</ref> | area = {{convert|81.45|km2|sqmi|abbr=on}}<ref name="knps.or.kr">{{cite web |url=http://english.knps.or.kr/Knp/Naejangsan/Intro/Introduction.aspx?MenuNum=1&Submenu=Npp |title=Naejangsan: Intro |author= |date= |website= |publisher=Korea National Park Service |accessdate=18 September 2010}}</ref> | established = 17 November 1971 | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = Korea National Park Service | world_heritage_site = | url = http://english.knps.or.kr/Knp/Naejangsan/Intro/Introduction.aspx }} {{South Korea national parks}} '''Naejangsan National Park''' ({{lang-ko|'''내장산국립공원''', '''內藏山國立公園'''}}) is located in the provinces of [[Jeollabuk-do]] and [[Jeollanam-do]], [[South Korea]]. It was designated as the 8th national park in 1971.<ref name="knps.or.kr" /> It is named after the {{convert|763|m|ft|adj=on}} mountain [[Naejangsan]].<ref name="knps.or.kr" /> The park is home to a total of 919 plant species and 1,880 animal species. 12 of the animals are endangered.<ref name="knps.or.kr" />
