{{Infobox settlement |name = Sigave |other_name = Sigavé / Singave |native_name = |settlement_type = Chiefdom and District |image_skyline = |imagesize = |image_caption = |image_flag = Flag of Sigave.svg |flag_size = 150px |flag_alt = |flag_link = Flag of Wallis and Futuna |image_seal = |image_shield = |shield_alt = |image_map = WF -Hoorn.png |map_caption = Sigave and Alo within the [[Hoorn Islands]] |pushpin_map = |pushpin_label_position = |pushpin_map_caption = |pushpin_mapsize=300 |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name = {{flag|France}} |subdivision_type1 = Territory |subdivision_name1 = {{flag|Wallis and Futuna|local}} |subdivision_type2 = Island |subdivision_name2 = [[Futuna (Wallis and Futuna)|Futuna]] |subdivision_type3 = Capital |subdivision_name3 = [[Leava]] |subdivision_type4 = |subdivision_name4 = |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = 30 |population_as_of = 2008 |population_footnotes = |population_total = 1,860 |population_density_km2 = 53 |timezone = [[UTC+12:00|UTC+12]] |utc_offset = |coordinates = {{coord|14|17|45.96|S|178|9|30.6|W|region:WF|display=inline,title}} |elevation_footnotes = |elevation_m = |blank_name_sec1 = No. of districts |blank_info_sec1 = 1 (Sigave)<ref>Coextensive with the chiefdom</ref> |blank1_name_sec1 = [[List of villages in Wallis and Futuna|No. of municipalities]] |blank1_info_sec1 = 6 |elevation_ft = |website = |footnotes = }}[[File:Futuna alofi.jpg|thumb|250px|Map of Hoorn Islands]] '''Sigavé''' (also '''Singave''' or '''Sigave''') is one of the three official [[chiefdom]]s of the [[France|French]] territory of [[Wallis and Futuna]] (the other two being [[Uvea (Wallis and Futuna)|Uvea]] and [[Alo (Wallis and Futuna)|Alo]]) in [[Oceania]] in the South [[Pacific Ocean]].
==Geography== ===Overview=== Sigave encompasses the western third (30 out of 83&nbsp;km²) of [[Futuna Island, Wallis and Futuna|Futuna Island]]. The total area of the kingdom is 30&nbsp;km², with a population of 1880, in six villages, as of the [[census]] of July 22, 2003. The [[Capital (political)|capital]] and largest village is [[Leava]] (pop. 480).
===Administrative division=== The chiefdom counts the homonym and coextensive district and 6 [[List of villages in Wallis and Futuna|municipalities]]:<ref>[http://www.insee.fr/fr/themes/detail.asp?ref_id=poplegalescom&page=recensement/poplegalescom/popvillwallisetfutuna.htm Municipal population of the villages in Wallis and Futuna] ([[INSEE]] 2008, complete list) {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130927161840/http://www.insee.fr/fr/themes/detail.asp?ref_id=poplegalescom&page=recensement%2Fpoplegalescom%2Fpopvillwallisetfutuna.htm |date=September 27, 2013 }}</ref>
