[[File:Timote gabashvili map detail.jpg|thumb|Detail from a map of Georgian coastal fortifications, by Timote Gabashvili, 1737]]
'''Timote (Timothy) Gabashvili''' ([[Georgian language|Georgian]]: ტიმოთე გაბაშვილი) (1703–1764) was a Georgian travel writer, traveler, diplomat, [[cartographer]], religious<ref>{{cite book |last1=Ebanoidze |first1=Mzia |last2=Wilkinson |first2=John|title=Pilgrimage: Timothy Gabashvili's Travels to Mount Athos, Constantinople and Jerusalem, 1755-1759 |series=Caucasus World |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4cQeAgAAQBAJ&pg=PP36 |accessdate=March 8, 2015 |year=2013 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-0700712649  |pages=36-37}}</ref> and public figure.{{citation needed|date=August 2011}} <ref>E. Metreveli., [[Georgian Soviet Encyclopedia]], vol. 2, pg. 604-605, Tb. Year 1977.</ref>

